@peterbreis5407 It's still pretty close imo. My question is : does it even matter? As a person looking to immigrate to AUS, every single city sounds amazing. I'm sure it's like that for most immigrants. At that point it's just a matter of affordability and the job market.

Myself, personally, am tied between the two. Sydney's weather is too great to pass up, the city itself is gorgeous and the liveliness reminds me of home, but at the same I also dislike the excessive crowds and fast-paced lifestyle. Also suuuper expensive.
The Melbourne art scene doesn't quite fascinate me that much (despite being an artsy person myself) and unpredictable weather make me a bit sad, but the laid-backness, affordability and diverse culture is great. I wonder if there's a city that has both of what I love in one place?

