@MrMorjo Essendon acts as a parallel set of runways for Tullamarine - close Essendon and Tullamarine is going to need two additional runways immediately to handle the Essendon traffic.
It can't be used for housing because of two words - Toxic Waste. The ground areas have been soaked in leaded petrol for fifty years, 130 octane Avgas (used in 1950's vintage piston engined airliners) will give you lead poisoning from breathing the vapour. The 100LL fuel used in light aircraft now is better but still has the same lead content as standard grade leaded petrol, with 87 octane now being mostly lead free.
Essendons runways and taxiways are built to handle a fully loaded 707. 2+m thick concrete is hard to shift.

