@lbell9695i have enjoyed visiting Sydney as a part Taswegian Melburnian….for seventy years. Love all the bling of Darling Harbour area, the Rocks and the beaches but outside the main city in the outskirts, it does nothing for me. Bar the Blue Mountains.

Tasmania is one huge adventure with amazing convict history, English villages and Georgian mansions, little tiny fishermen’s houses like in Arthur’s Circle. Salamanca Market. Love it. The red granite rocks in the north east, the Tasman Peninsula, Freycinet, Mount Wellington, the Great Lakes and Cradle Mountain. As a child growing up there, we did Sunday drives every weekend and I took it all for granted. A wonderful display on the almost extinct local aborigines in the Queen Victoria Museum so at last they are being acknowledged.

Melbourne I equally adore. I’ve decided that I wouldn’t live anywhere else. Except perhaps Prince Edward Island, Canada. You must go there too.

